        <h2>Fees and Payment</h2>
        <p>
          Fees for services are agreed upon in writing before work commences. Payment terms include:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Invoicing:</strong> Invoices are issued according to agreed schedule</li>
          <li><strong>Payment Terms:</strong> Typically 14-30 days from invoice date</li>
          <li><strong>Late Payment:</strong> Late payments may incur interest charges</li>
          <li><strong>Expenses:</strong> Reasonable expenses may be charged in addition to fees</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Confidentiality</h2>
        <p>
          We maintain strict confidentiality regarding client information:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>All client information is treated as confidential</li>
          <li>Information is not disclosed without client consent (except as required by law)</li>
          <li>Confidentiality obligations survive termination of the engagement</li>
          <li>Anonymized examples may be used for training or marketing purposes</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Intellectual Property</h2>

        <h3>Client Materials</h3>
        <p>
          Clients retain ownership of materials they provide to us. We use these materials solely for providing services.
        </p>

        <h3>Deliverables</h3>
        <p>
          Ownership of work product created during the engagement is typically addressed in the service agreement. Unless otherwise agreed:
