          <li>Timely payment of fees</li>
          <li>Making their own business decisions</li>
          <li>Implementing recommendations appropriately</li>
          <li>Complying with applicable laws and regulations</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Termination</h2>

        <h3>By Either Party</h3>
        <p>
          Either party may terminate an engagement with written notice as specified in the service agreement, typically:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>14-30 days' notice for ongoing engagements</li>
          <li>Immediate termination for material breach</li>
          <li>Payment for work completed up to termination date</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Effect of Termination</h3>
        <p>
          Upon termination:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>All outstanding fees become immediately due</li>
          <li>Confidentiality obligations continue</li>
          <li>We will return or destroy client materials as requested</li>
          <li>We provide work completed to date</li>
        </ul>

